[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626791&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626791&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

Do people use GATEWAY PTRs as described on the bottom of page 10
of rfc1033?  What are you supposed to do in the presence of subnets
and gateways which route only between subnets?  For example, if
G is a gateway between 128.n.a.0 and 128.n.b.0 should this be listed
in a RR

n.128.in-addr.arpa  and/or
a.n.128.in-addr.arpa and/or
b.n.128.in-addr.arpa   ?


Are there patches to Bind 4.8 that are later than the tar version
on ucbarpa (Aug. 88)?

Steve Hubert
University of Washington
hubert@cac.washington.edu

